  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 27 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 8 critical, 10 high, 13 medium, 8 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB); plus 15 other bases. 13 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT). Network hotspots: Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), İstanbul (IST/LTFM), Brussels South Charleroi (CRL/EBCI), Cologne Bonn (CGN/EDDK) and 22 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 4 airports changed status, led by Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI), Ohrid St. Paul the Apostle (OHD/LWOH) and 1 others.",
